channel.title: Compiler error
channel.description:
When i run my compiler it says this.
[code]client.java:9758: cannot find symbol symbol : variable kickownerowntk location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickownerowntk = victim; ^ client.java:9767: cannot find symbol symbol : variable kickownerowntk location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickownerowntk = victim; ^ client.java:11794: cannot find symbol symbol : class kickowner location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickowner owntk = null; ^ client.java:11799: cannot find symbol symbol : variable kickownerowntk location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickownerowntk = command.substring(5); ^ client.java:12034: cannot find symbol symbol : class kickowner location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickowner owntk = command. substring(5); ^ client.java:12040: cannot find symbol symbol : variable kickownerowntk location: class PlayerHandler bw.write(playerName+" kicked "+PlayerHandler.kickownerowntk); ^ client.java:12056: cannot find symbol symbol : variable kickownerowntk location: class PlayerHandler bw.write(playerName+" kicked "+PlayerHandler.kickownerowntk); ^ client.java:18008: cannot find symbol symbol : class kickowner location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickowner owntk = p5.playerName; ^ client.java:18046: cannot find symbol symbol : class kickowner location: class PlayerHandler PlayerHandler.kickowner owntk = p5.playerName; ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 9 errors Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
How do i fix this! Thanks

item.title: Compiler error
item.dc:creator: @Jellybean732 Jellybean732
item.description:
@Jellybean732 wrote:

Well it’s looking for something in your PlayerHandler - kickowner. So go into your PlayerHandler.java file and search for kickowner owntk

If it exists post what it says and I’ll have a look at it. If it doesn’t exist then your server’s looking for something that isn’t there so just delete looking for it from line (ctrl + G) 9758 and anywhere else it appears in your client.java if you don’t need it.

If you do want it then your gonna have to create a boolean, public int or something else which could be more complicated. Get back to me…
